description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have the passion and knowledge to provide excellent care to acute respiratory, gastroenterology, endocrine and general medical patients? Do you place value on teamwork, communication and excellent career development? If so come and join our exciting new ward team based here at The Royal Bournemouth Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ward will be taking admissions straight from AMU for gastroenterology, endocrine, respiratory and general medical patients. The patients admitted to the ward will have a variety of medical conditions allowing you the opportunity to utilise and develop the skills required to care for this group of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at RBCH we pride ourselves on offering opportunities for career development ranging from Band 2 to band 4 Associate Practitioners and moving through to band 5 Registered Nurses and higher.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What can &lt;strong&gt;We&lt;/strong&gt; offer you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A wide variety of shifts including permanent nights and weekends, with full or part time work patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So please come and join our amazing team in the Medical Care Group!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will commence on the winter care ward for 6 months and then once the ward has closed the position will be within the medical care group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 17th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Carl Corbridge Atkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Title: Clinical Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: carl.corbridge-atkins@rbch.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone Number: 0300 019 4495&lt;/p&gt;
